quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  63,5,"And when it is said to them, “Come, the Messenger of Allah will ask forgiveness for you,” they keep turning1 their heads aside and yousg see them turning away while acting arrogantly."
  63,6,"It is the same for them whether yousg ask forgiveness for them or do not ask forgiveness for them—Allah will not forgive them; indeed, Allah does not guide the defiantly disobedient people."
  63,7,"It is they who say: “Do not spend anything on those who side with Allah’s Messenger, that they may disperse.” And to Allah belong the treasuries of the heavens and the earth, but the hypocrites do not comprehend."
  63,8,"They say, “If we return to al-Madinah, the mightier ones will surely evict the inferior ones.” But might belongs to Allah and His Messenger and the believers, but the hypocrites do not know."
  63,9,"O you who have attained faith, let neither your wealth nor your children distract you from the remembrance of Allah, and whoever does that—then those are the losers."
  63,10,"And spend from what We have provided for youpl before death approaches one of you, whereupon he says, “My Lord, if only You would delay me for a short while so that I may donate and become of the righteous!”"